{"_env":"NODEJS","_serializationMethod":"normal","_autosave":false,"_autosaveInterval":5000,"_collections":[{"name":"items","unindexedSortComparator":"js","defaultLokiOperatorPackage":"js","_dynamicViews":[],"uniqueNames":[],"transforms":{},"rangedIndexes":{},"_data":[{"slug":"hello-world","description":"My first blog post.","id":"4F51FA8B-B7A5-402F-A6A6-58E6F8CFF023","title":"Hello, World!","date":"2022-01-13T10:22:00.000Z","toc":[],"body":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Hi there, hello, I'm Thom. Thom Bruce. But if you're here, you probably already know that. Hey, what do you expect? It's my first blog post; introductions are in order. So, I'm Thom and this is my blog. A reboot of it anyway. I don't really know what my endgame is for it, for this site, for my whole... online persona... but I want to take a fresh approach. And so, I am starting from scratch."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A bit about me, then. I'm... a programmer, currently working with a health sector client and the NHS. I'm a father; beautiful little dude called Ethan - he's five. I want to be a writer but I haven't done enough of it in a decade to justify calling myself one. And I'm an avid gamer and cinema fan; a lot of geekdom stuff, really - comics, cartoons and novel technologies. Speaking of which, I do know that I want to focus on writing about precisely that here: novel technologies. This site is a serverless, static website on what we call the Jamstack. That's... pretty novel. Really what it is is cheap and environmentally friendly. Y'know, you don't need a server to host blog content... or to make it searchable.... It's... largely unchanging. Meanwhile, the JA in 'JAMstack' stands for JavaScript and APIs. We can take a best of both worlds approach, where blog content and search is static, but we can still add dynamic features like... I dunno, chat maybe. We can do that using JavaScript enhancement, coupled with external APIs. I mean we'll go into it in time... "},{"type":"element","tag":"em","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I'm rambling."}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I'm lost. I don't know if there's "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A LOT"}]},{"type":"text","value":" more to know about me or "},{"type":"element","tag":"em","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"nothing at all"}]},{"type":"text","value":". There are a lot of projects I would like to list that are in various states of development, from ideation to functional prototype, from ready for production to waiting to come out of long-hiatus. I'm not gonna do that here. And I have a bunch of hobbies and interests I could talk about, but maybe we'll get to those in time. Honestly, my mind is terribly scattered. In a way, I consider "},{"type":"element","tag":"em","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"a blog"}]},{"type":"text","value":" the first step towards bringing my thoughts under control. We've got a lot to talk about..."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Hope you stick around."}]}]},"text":"\nHi there, hello, I'm Thom. Thom Bruce. But if you're here, you probably already know that. Hey, what do you expect? It's my first blog post; introductions are in order. So, I'm Thom and this is my blog. A reboot of it anyway. I don't really know what my endgame is for it, for this site, for my whole... online persona... but I want to take a fresh approach. And so, I am starting from scratch.\n\nA bit about me, then. I'm... a programmer, currently working with a health sector client and the NHS. I'm a father; beautiful little dude called Ethan - he's five. I want to be a writer but I haven't done enough of it in a decade to justify calling myself one. And I'm an avid gamer and cinema fan; a lot of geekdom stuff, really - comics, cartoons and novel technologies. Speaking of which, I do know that I want to focus on writing about precisely that here: novel technologies. This site is a serverless, static website on what we call the Jamstack. That's... pretty novel. Really what it is is cheap and environmentally friendly. Y'know, you don't need a server to host blog content... or to make it searchable.... It's... largely unchanging. Meanwhile, the JA in 'JAMstack' stands for JavaScript and APIs. We can take a best of both worlds approach, where blog content and search is static, but we can still add dynamic features like... I dunno, chat maybe. We can do that using JavaScript enhancement, coupled with external APIs. I mean we'll go into it in time... _I'm rambling._\n\nI'm lost. I don't know if there's **A LOT** more to know about me or _nothing at all_. There are a lot of projects I would like to list that are in various states of development, from ideation to functional prototype, from ready for production to waiting to come out of long-hiatus. I'm not gonna do that here. And I have a bunch of hobbies and interests I could talk about, but maybe we'll get to those in time. Honestly, my mind is terribly scattered. In a way, I consider _a blog_ the first step towards bringing my thoughts under control. We've got a lot to talk about...\n\nHope you stick around.","dir":"/blog","path":"/blog/hello-world","extension":".md","createdAt":"2022-01-13T11:29:47.509Z","updatedAt":"2022-01-13T11:29:47.509Z","meta":{"version":0,"revision":0,"created":1642073486777},"$loki":1}],"idIndex":[1],"maxId":1,"_dirty":true,"_nestedProperties":[],"transactional":false,"asyncListeners":false,"disableMeta":false,"disableChangesApi":true,"disableDeltaChangesApi":true,"cloneObjects":false,"cloneMethod":"deep","changes":[],"_fullTextSearch":{"ii":{"title":{"_store":true,"_optimizeChanges":true,"docCount":1,"docStore":[[0